    <!-- About Section -->
    <section class="section" id="about">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">What is Power Systems Engineering?</h2>
            <div class="content-wrapper">
                <div class="text-content">
                    <p>Power Systems Engineering is a specialized branch of electrical engineering that focuses on the generation, transmission, distribution, and utilization of electric power. It encompasses the study of equipment, devices, and systems that convert, transform, and deliver electricity from power plants to end users.</p>
                    <p>As a power systems engineer, you'll work on designing and maintaining the infrastructure that powers our modern world, from massive power plants and high-voltage transmission lines to distribution networks and smart grid technologies. You'll also address challenges related to power quality, system stability, protection, and the integration of renewable energy sources.</p>
                    <p>This field combines principles of electrical engineering with aspects of mechanical engineering, civil engineering, economics, and environmental science to ensure reliable, efficient, and sustainable power delivery.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="image-content">
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1473341304170-971dccb5ac1e?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80" alt="Power Systems Engineering">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Areas Section -->
    <section class="section bg-light" id="key-areas">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">Key Areas of Study</h2>
            <p class="section-intro">Power Systems Engineering encompasses several specialized areas that work together to ensure reliable and efficient electrical power delivery:</p>
            
            <div class="cards-grid three-columns">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-industry"></i> Power Generation</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of converting various forms of energy (thermal, hydro, nuclear, solar, wind) into electrical energy. This includes understanding generators, prime movers, power plant operations, and renewable energy technologies.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Conventional Generation</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Thermal, hydro, and nuclear power plants</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Renewable Generation</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Solar, wind, biomass, and geothermal systems</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Generator Technology</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Synchronous machines, induction generators</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-broadcast-tower"></i> Transmission Systems</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of transporting electrical energy from generation plants to distribution systems over long distances. This includes high-voltage transmission lines, substations, and system stability analysis.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Transmission Line Theory</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Line parameters, models, and performance</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">HVDC Systems</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">High-voltage direct current transmission</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Substation Design</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Equipment selection, layout, protection</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-network-wired"></i> Distribution Systems</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of delivering electrical energy from transmission systems to end users. This includes medium and low-voltage networks, transformers, and distribution automation.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Distribution Network Design</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Radial and loop systems, reliability</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Distribution Automation</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">SCADA, fault location, service restoration</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Load Management</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Demand response, peak shaving</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="cards-grid three-columns" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Power System Protection</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of detecting and isolating faults to prevent damage to equipment and ensure system reliability. This includes protective relays, circuit breakers, and coordination studies.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Protective Relaying</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Overcurrent, distance, differential protection</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Fault Analysis</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Symmetrical and asymmetrical faults</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Coordination Studies</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Selectivity, sensitivity, reliability</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> Power System Analysis</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of modeling and analyzing power systems under steady-state and dynamic conditions. This includes load flow studies, stability analysis, and economic operation.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Load Flow Analysis</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Power flow calculations and voltage profiles</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Stability Analysis</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Transient, dynamic, and voltage stability</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Economic Dispatch</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Optimal generation allocation and cost minimization</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-brain"></i> Smart Grid Technologies</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of modernizing power grids with digital communication, automation, and control technologies. This includes advanced metering, demand response, and grid integration of distributed resources.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Advanced Metering Infrastructure</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Smart meters, data management, analytics</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Distributed Energy Resources</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Integration of solar, storage, and microgrids</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Grid Automation</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Self-healing networks, adaptive protection</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

